    "text": "Anaemia",
    "level": 1
  },
  {
    "type": "callout",
    "text": "Definition: Reduction in oxygen carrying capacity of blood secondary to decreased level of circulating red blood cells and haemoglobin."
  },
  {
    "type": "tab_group",
    "tabs": [
      {
        "title": "Basics & Causes",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "header",
            "text": "Pathophysiological Mechanisms",
            "level": 2
          },
          {
            "type": "list",
            "items": [
              { "text": "Material Deficiency (Iron, B12, Folate)" },
              { "text": "Marrow Failure / Ineffective Erythropoiesis" },
              { "text": "RBC Loss (Bleeding) or Destruction (Haemolysis)" }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "header",
            "text": "Flash Card 20: Causes of Anaemia",
            "level": 2
          },
          {
            "type": "accordion",
            "items": [
              {
                "title": "Reduced RBC Production",
                "content": [
                  { "type": "list", "items": [
                    { "text": "Marrow Failure: Aplastic Anaemia, Myelodysplasia" },
                    { "text": "Dysfunction: Anaemia of Chronic Disease (CKD, CLD, Chronic Infection/Inflammation)" },
                    { "text": "Infiltrative: Leukaemia, Myeloma, Metastasis, Myelofibrosis" },
                    { "text": "Endocrine: Hypothyroidism, Addison's disease" }
                  ]}
                ]
              },
              {
                "title": "Essential Nutrient Deficiency",
                "content": [
                  { "type": "list", "items": [
                    { "text": "Iron Deficiency: Poor diet, Pregnancy, Blood loss (GI/Uterine), Malabsorption" },
                    { "text": "B12 Deficiency: Pernicious Anaemia, Ileal disease/resection, Vegans" },
                    { "text": "Folate Deficiency: Drugs (Methotrexate), Pregnancy, Malabsorption" }
                  ]}
                ]
              },
              {
                "title": "Increased Destruction / Loss",
                "content": [
                  { "type": "list", "items": [
                    { "text": "Corpuscular (Intrinsic): Membrane (Spherocytosis), Enzyme (G6PD), Hb (Thalassaemia)" },
                    { "text": "Extra-Corpuscular (Extrinsic): Autoimmune (Warm/Cold), Drugs, Malaria, Microangiopathy (DIC/TTP)" },
                    { "text": "Blood Loss: Acute (Trauma) or Chronic (Hookworm, Peptic Ulcer)" }
                  ]}
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "header",
            "text": "Flash Card 21: Morphological Classification",
            "level": 2
          },
          {
            "type": "table",
            "tableHeaders": ["Type", "Causes"],
            "tableRows": [
              ["Hypochromic Microcytic", "• Iron Deficiency\n• Thalassaemia\n• Sideroblastic Anaemia\n• Anaemia of Chronic Disease (some cases)"],
              ["Normochromic Normocytic", "• Aplastic Anaemia\n• Acute Blood Loss\n• Anaemia of Chronic Disease\n• Renal Failure\n• Marrow Infiltration"],
              ["Macrocytic", "• Megaloblastic: B12/Folate Deficiency\n• Normoblastic: Liver Disease, Hypothyroidism, Alcoholism, Myelodysplasia"]
            ]
          }
        ]
